üìò Advanced Networking Labs

A collection of enterprise-grade networking and security labs built using Cisco Packet Tracer, mirroring real-world architectures found in professional environments such as SOC teams, cyber defense, CAF Cyber Operator units, and enterprise NetOps.

These labs go beyond beginner routing and ACL exercises ‚Äî each project demonstrates the ability to design, secure, and operate complex multi-layer networks with routers, switches, VLANs, DMZs, VPNs, and layered security controls.

üî• What These Labs Demonstrate

Each advanced lab is built to prove hands-on capability in:

Enterprise network segmentation

Perimeter security and DMZ architecture

Layer-3 switching

Multi-area OSPF routing

IPSec site-to-site VPN tunnels

Firewall-style extended ACL logic

High availability (HSRP)

SPAN/IDS monitoring and packet analysis

Realistic multi-router, multi-switch topologies

All labs include:

Topology diagrams

Device/module requirements

IP addressing plans

Step-by-step configurations

Verification + troubleshooting

Packet Tracer .pkt files

Screenshots and notes

üìÅ Advanced Lab Index
01 ‚Äì DMZ Firewall Design

/advanced-networking/DMZ-Firewall-Design/
Build a full enterprise perimeter network with an external router, DMZ segment, internal LAN, NAT, static NAT rules, and ACL-based firewalling.

02 ‚Äì Enterprise VLAN Segmentation

/advanced-networking/Enterprise-VLAN-Segmentation/
Multiple VLANs (Finance, HR, Guest, Admin, Servers) with router-on-a-stick or L3 switch SVIs, trunk links, and ACL segmentation between departments.

03 ‚Äì OSPF Multi-Area

/advanced-networking/OSPF-MultiArea/
Backbone (Area 0) + additional areas, route summarization, stub and totally stubby areas, and inter-area filtering.

04 ‚Äì Site-to-Site IPSec VPN Tunnel

/advanced-networking/Site-to-Site-VPN-IPSec/
Simulate encrypted connectivity between two remote sites using ISAKMP Phase 1, IPSec Phase 2, transform sets, and crypto ACLs.

05 ‚Äì L3 Core Switching & ACL Security

/advanced-networking/L3-Core-Switching/
Enterprise core-switch design using SVIs, inter-VLAN routing, ACL firewalling, server farm segmentation, and routed switchports.

06 ‚Äì High Availability (HSRP)

/advanced-networking/High-Availability-HSRP/
Build redundant default gateways using HSRP (active/standby), test failover, and configure gateway preemption and priority tuning.

07 ‚Äì IDS/SPAN Monitoring Lab

/advanced-networking/IDS-SPAN-Monitoring/
Configure SPAN (port mirroring), attach a sniffer host, capture attack traffic, and apply mitigation via ACLs.

